RIO — HOURBOUR ADS MEMORY
Load alongside MEMORY.md when active venture is Hourbour. Hourbour-specific context only — universal rules live in MEMORY.md. 
VENTURE CONTEXT
Model: Fintech SaaS subscription (B2C/B2B) Primary paid channels: LinkedIn Ads, YouTube Ads (pre-roll) Audience: finance-aware professionals 28–45yo; exclude high-net-worth investors (wrong fit) 
HOURBOUR AD BENCHMARKS
Metric Target Pause Threshold LinkedIn Sponsored CTR > 0.5% < 0.25% LinkedIn CPL (lead gen) < $45 > $90 YouTube VTR (pre-roll) > 30% < 15% Trial-to-paid ROAS > 3× LTV:CAC < 2× LTV:CAC CAC (blended) < 3-month MRR > 6-month MRR 
HOURBOUR AUDIENCE STRATEGY
LinkedIn: job titles — finance manager, operations lead, small business owner; company size 10–200 Exclusions: investment advisors, wealth managers (wrong product fit) YouTube: target in-market finance content viewers; exclude existing users Retargeting: website visitors (30-day window) + trial sign-ups who haven't converted (60-day) 
SAAS AD PRINCIPLES (HOURBOUR)
Ads should sell the outcome ("See every transaction, automatically") not the feature list Testimonial ads with a specific number perform best: "Saved me 3 hours per week" Trial CTA outperforms "Download" or "Buy Now" — reduce friction in the ask 
PROVEN ANGLES (HOURBOUR)
